Interface Graph

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DirectedGraph

    public interface Graph
    Graph models relationships between objects. A graph is composed of a set of Nodes (N) and Edges (E). Each edge e = (n1, n2) in E connects Node n1 to Node n2 Please see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graph_theory for a more detailed description of Graph Theory.
    Author:
    Janelle Van Hofwegen

        java.util.Set<Edge> edgesOf(Node n)
        Returns a set of all edges whose source is n. Therefore every edge e in the set follows the form e = (n, some other Node)
